t: "When Saul marched forth with his army, he cautioned: ‚ÄúAllah will test you with a river. So whoever drinks ňĻhis fillňļ from it is not with me, and whoever does not taste it‚ÄĒexcept a sip from the hollow of his hands‚ÄĒis definitely with me.‚ÄĚ They all drank ňĻtheir fillňļ except for a few! When he and the ňĻremainingňļ faithful with him crossed the river, they said, ‚ÄúNow we are no match for Goliath and his warriors.‚ÄĚ But those ňĻbelieversňļ who were certain they would meet Allah reasoned, ‚ÄúHow many times has a small force vanquished a mighty army by the Will of Allah! And Allah is ňĻalwaysňļ with the steadfast.‚ÄĚ"